<p><br>
<font color="#ffffff" size="3"><strong><u>Event Lotto Point</u></strong></font>
<p><font color="#ffffff" size="1">Event Lotto Point (ELPs) are
points members can gain on all guild events. These points can
then be spent on items that drop during the events.</font> </p>

<p><font color="#ffffff" size="1">The reason for using ELP system
is to reward total effort and participation in guild events and
to prevent bad lotto's. A bad lotto is when someone wins
something over others and everyone or the majority of the people
present agree that the winner should not have won.</font> </p>

<p><font color="#ffffff" size="3"><em><strong>How does someone
gain ELPs? </strong></em></font></p>

<p><font color="#ffffff" size="1">All events will have a point
value assigned to them.</font> </p>

<p><font color="#ffffff" size="1">What defines a &quot;ELP
Event&quot; A event will have all of the following
characteristics:</font> <br>
<font color="#ffffff" size="1">1. Consist of no less then 18 IC
members.</font> <br>
<font color="#ffffff" size="1">2. Be lead by an IC member.</font>
<br>
<font color="#ffffff" size="1">3. Must be a creature of medium
difficulty.</font> </p>

<p><font color="#ffffff" size="3"><em><strong>How do ELPs and
lotto's work together?</strong></em></font><font size="3"><em><strong>
</strong></em></font></p>

<font color="#ffffff" size="1">It is quite simple actually.
Any item that drops is given an initial bid value by officers
present at the raid.
<br>Each person who can use will be able to bid on that item. 
<br>Certain restrictions might be put into effect due to some having more of a benefit of that item.
<br>There is times when some items will be auctioned to those present regardless if they can use or not.</font></p>

<p><font color="#ffffff" size="3"><em><strong>I'm unfamiliar with
auctions. How do they work?</strong></em></font></p>

<p><font color="#ffffff" size="1">There are 2 types of auctions:</font></p>

<p><font color="#ffffff" size="1"><strong><u>Basic Auction</u></strong>
<br>Item has initial amount. The one auctioning will say a number
and ask if anyone wishes to bid this amount.<br>
Either send a tell or speak up in /say. All auctions are final.</font></p>

<p><font color="#ffffff" size="1"><strong><u>Dutch Auctions</u></strong>
<br>Simple once you understand the concept. Dutch auction consists
of 2 or more of the same item dropping.<br>
The 2 highest bids win the item at the LOWEST of the 2 bid.<br>
If &quot;A&quot; bids 10 and &quot;B&quot; bids 11, you would need to at least bid 11 to now have a chance at that
item.
<br>
If the final bidding is at 11 and 12, both pay the lower which is 11.</font></p>

<p><font color="#ffffff" size="3"><em><strong>Lotto Eligibility:</strong></em></font><font
size="3"><em><strong> </strong></em></font><br>
<font color="#ffffff" size="1">1. Mains will never have to lotto
vs. twinks regardless of points.</font> <br>
<font color="#ffffff" size="1">2. Anyone who can and will benefit
from a item can enter. There are cases where a item will drop
that can be used by many classes, but would be better used by one
class. Officers or raid leaders will use their own judgment in
these cases.</font> </p>

<p><font color="#ffffff" size="3"><em><strong>Items won on ELP
events:</strong></em></font><font size="3"><em><strong> </strong></em></font><br>
<font color="#ffffff" size="1">These items cannot be given to
twinks or traded to other players. If someone no longer needs a
item they can lotto that item at the next ELP event and receive
back the points spent on the item. If for some reason no one
wants the item at the next ELP the owner may choose to wait and
try again next raid or give the item to the guild fund and
receive back half the points the item cost. Another option is to
put the item on the guild trading auction board as well.</font></p>

<p><font color="#ffffff" size="3"><em><strong>Extra ELP items:</strong></em></font><font
size="3"><em><strong> </strong></em></font><br>
<font color="#ffffff" size="1">All extra items will go to the
guild fund and a officer will attempt to trade these for other
items a mains need. If after a reasonable amount of time, these
items are still in the guild fund, they will be put on the ELP
Auction Board. If a no drop item drops and no mains need the item
will be lottoed to any twinks. These items will cost ELP either
by auction type system or a set value set by officers at the
raid.</font> </p>

<p><font color="#ffffff" size="3"><em><strong>Can you enter lotto
vs. other mains if you are not present when the item drops?</strong></em></font><font
size="3"><em><strong> </strong></em></font><br>
<font color="#ffffff" size="1">Yes, but only when the following
is true:</font> <br>
<font color="#ffffff" size="1">1. You have enough points to buy
the item.</font> <br>
<font color="#ffffff" size="1">2. The person present is currently
in the negative range.</font> </p>

